r\nlose our balance and our judgment gets badly beated. This may result in fur=\r\nther bad karmas being committed in that agitated/confused state.\n=C2=A0\nThu=\r\ns, it IS sometimes useful to push off some really bad impending karmas when=\r\n one is still in a position to do so. If one reaches a calmer state of mind=\r\n in that borrowed time, one may be able to handle the bad fruits better. It=\r\n is even possible theoretically that one pushes off a really bad karma, mak=\r\nes progress during that borrowed time, reaches an equanimous state of mind,=\r\n becomes liberated and then faces the karma as a liberated being with a tot=\r\nally equanimous mind that does not get agitated.\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=\r\n=A0\nComment 2: Prarabda karma is which was already done and sanchitha and a=\r\ngami are what we going to do.\n=C2=A0\nMy Response: Actually sanchita karmas =\r\nare also karmas already done. Sanchita means &quot;piled up&quot;. Prarabdha karmas a=\r\nre different in the sense that their fructification has already begun. The =\r\nverb &quot;prArabh&quot; means &quot;to begin&quot;. Its noun form &quot;prArambha&quot; means &quot;beginning=\r\n&quot; and its gerund noun form &quot;prArabdha&quot; means &quot;the [one that was] begun&quot;. Pr=\r\narabdha karmas are actions for which the process of reaction has already be=\r\ngun and in the pipeline. Whereas sanchita karmas are piled up karmas that h=\r\nave not kicked off their fruits yet. They can be delayed indefinitely. If o=\r\nne becomes liberated while living, one can merge in Cosmic Self without exp=\r\neriencing the fruits of sanchita karmas. However, fruits of prarabdha karma=\r\ns are already in the pipeline and need to be experienced even by a liberate=\r\nd being.\n=C2=A0\nThough fruits of prarabdha karmas are already in the pipeli=\r\nne, even they can actually be delayed or manipulated. Bottomline is that th=\r\nere are agents of delivery at the physical and subtle level even for things=\r\n deep in the pipeline and hence some limited adjustment is possible.\n\n=C2=\r\n=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nComment 3:How does nishkam karma works? In othe=\r\nr words, when a doer detaches himself from an action, where does the reacti=\r\non goes?\n=C2=A0\nMy Response: If one identifies with a body-mind complex and=\r\n a limited sense of self-identification and pursues its selfish agenda, one=\r\n keeps accumulating karmas. But, if one has minimal identification with a b=\r\nody-mind complex to just sustain it, pursues no agenda and engages in whate=\r\nver action is natural in the situation one is in (but not driven by any con=\r\nditioning, i.e.agendas or desires or likes/dislikes), then one is untouched=\r\n by karmas performed in that state.\n=C2=A0\nIn the words of Swami Sivananda =\r\nof Hrishikesh, &quot;The accumulated and current actions of a Jnani take shelter=\r\n in Brahmanda Prakriti&quot;. In other words, Sanchita karmas (piled up actions =\r\nfrom past that have not yet begun fructifying) and aagami karmas (actions b=\r\neing performed right now) of a liberated being take shelted in Cosmic Kinet=\r\nic Consciousness (Brahmanda Prakriti).\n\n=C2=A0*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nCommen=\r\nt 4: If my destiny is to suffer, why should I pray to God? And if i am bein=\r\ng \npunished for some kind of bad karma from the past, why am i not aware of=\r\n it? It is like getting punishment without knowing your bad deeds.\n=C2=A0\nM=\r\ny Response: One need not pray to God.All one needs to do is to stop engagin=\r\ng in problematic karmas to add to the pile of such karmas from the past. Mo=\r\nre importantly, one needs to reach a calm and sustainable state of mind in =\r\nwhich that can be maintained even in the middle of a tumultous hurricane ca=\r\nused in one&#39;s life due to serious bad karmas from the past. Once serious tr=\r\noubles set in or mind focuses on sense objects, material world and one&#39;s pl=\r\neasures and pains, mind tends to lose its balance and judgment, starts purs=\r\nuing its limited selfish agendas and starts performing even more bad karmas=\r\n. Thus, praying to God and contemplating various ideals and qualities that =\r\nGod represents can give a shelter to the mind in which it can maintain some=\r\n calmness, balance and judgment. If that is not the case for one, perhaps o=\r\nne needs to perfect it further.\n=C2=A0\nGod has no agenda to either punish y=\r\nou or hide the reason. God is an impartial balancer of reactions to all act=\r\nions. If there is something unreasonable about the reaction you are getting=\r\n, it means your action had a similar unreasonableness.\n\n=C2=A0Let me turn a=\r\nround your question on being &quot;aware&quot; and ask a simple question. When we cau=\r\nse loss or hurt to someone, do we always tell that person why we are doing =\r\nit? If not, how can we expect someone to tell us before causing loss or hur=\r\nt to us? If I caused terrible strife to someone pious and pure for no reaso=\r\nn, then Nature will use someone in future to cause terrible strife to me de=\r\nspite my piety and purity and apparently for no reason.\n=C2=A0\nIn fact, wha=\r\nt will you achieve by knowing exactly what was the action that caused what =\r\nis happening to you right now? Why is that useful? More useful is your cons=\r\ncience (a representation of God in each heart) that tells you right from wr=\r\nong. It constantly gives guidance on which actions will give good reactions=\r\n *in future*.\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nComment 5: Vasana can be for wea=\r\nlth, fame, power, domination (a struggle for power!) etc.Many ripus, many r=\r\neasons...!\n=C2=A0\nMy Response: Well-said. Though we are discussing karma an=\r\nd karma phala here, the root cause of karma is vasana in chittaakasha. (Chi=\r\ndaakaasha is the space of pure consciousness and chittaakaasha is the space=\r\n of conditioned consciousness that has likes, dislikes, desires, agendas et=\r\nc.) Vasishtha defined liberation as overcoming vasanas in Yoga Vaasishtham =\r\nand Patanjali defined yoga as &quot;chitta vR^itti nirodhaH yogaH&quot; (resisting th=\r\ne working of conditioning is oneness with Cosmic Self) in Yoga Sutras. Unti=\r\nl we overcome our vasanas, we are bound. Some are dense and some are very s=\r\nubtle. But all of them bind us.\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nComment 6:1.=\r\n As per Shri Vimalananda, you may also offer all the karmas as Homa to inne=\r\nr \ndevas or ishta devta? He mentioned that there is lesser of suffering if =\r\n\nyou do that. Who gets the remaining delta suffering?\n=C2=A0\nMy Response: K=\r\narmaphala for a specific karma is not a function of that karma alone. It is=\r\n a function of that karma and one&#39;s current state of mind. If someone serve=\r\ns spoiled food, one may get an upset stomach for half day or diaria for a w=\r\neek. It depends on how strong one is. Similarly, the same karmaphala set in=\r\n motion by the same external agents of delivery (physical & subtle) can cau=\r\nse different reaction inside one, depending on one&#39;s current state of mind.=\r\n\n=C2=A0\nAn idle mind is devil&#39;s workshop. Our minds keep vibrating with var=\r\nious notions and thoughts. A mind vibrating with selfish desires and unnece=\r\nssary clutter/confusion *amplifies* the negative effects of one&#39;s environme=\r\nnt (through which fruits of karmas are administered).\n=C2=A0\nIf one thinks =\r\nof ishta devata with reverence and contemplates various ideals and qualitie=\r\ns of ishta devata and mind vibrates with saattwik energy, it absorbs the ne=\r\ngative effects of one&#39;s environment better or atleast does not amplify them=\r\n.\n=C2=A0\nBest regards,\nNarasimha\n--------\nAstrology & Spirituality Resource=\r\ns: http://www.VedicAstrologer.org\n--------\n\n=C2=A0\n\n\n&gt;_____________________=\r\n___________\n&gt; From: Narasimha P.V.R. Rao &lt;pvr108@...&gt;\n&gt;To: Vedic Wisd=\r\nom &lt;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&gt; \n&gt;Sent: Sunday, March 3, 2013 5:26 PM\n&gt;Su=\r\nbject: Karma, Phala, Remedies, Blessings, Curses etc (Re: few questions)\n&gt; =\r\n\n&gt;\n&gt;Namaste friends,\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;Ajit&#39;s reply to Digamber ji&#39;s nice questions =\r\nis thoughtful. I will add my 2 cents.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;*=C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0=C2=A0 =\r\n*=C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;=C2=A0The cosmos runs based on the fundament=\r\nal law that each action (karma) gives a reaction/result (karmaphala) commen=\r\nsurate with it. Shakti is the sum total of all the beings with various agen=\r\ndas engaging in various karmas and experiencing various karmaphalas. Purush=\r\na is the witness of it all.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;Though each karma should give karmapha=\r\nla that is commensurate with it, that requires an *agent* to deliver the ka=\r\nrmaphala, i.e. another being. So this requires a complicated balancing act =\r\non part of Cosmic Cumulative Kinetic Consciousness (i.e. Shakti). There are=\r\n very complicated rules that decide the *sequencing* of karmaphalas and pic=\r\nking of agents for their delivery.\n&gt;\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;At any time, some karmas from=\r\n one&#39;s past are placed in a &quot;must experience karmaphala in this life&quot; pool,=\r\n some karmas in a &quot;preferably experience karmaphala in this life&quot; pool and =\r\nthe rest in the third pool which may not be experienced anytime soon. The w=\r\nay karmas are assigned and ordered in these pools is based on the balancing=\r\n of karma/karmaphala sequencing of all beings.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;The assignment and =\r\nordering of these pools will constantly undergo churn as one engages in var=\r\nious new actions and adds them to the pools. Also, as new people enter one&#39;=\r\ns life, possibilities in terms of karmaphala delivery agents and sequencing=\r\n may change and hence the pools may be re-arranged.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 =\r\n*\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;As one engages in remedial measures such as prayers, fasting, do=\r\nnations etc, one may transform one&#39;s nature, change one&#39;s vulnerabilities o=\r\nr re-arrange one&#39;s dynamics with other beings (including planets, deities e=\r\ntc, who are the subtle agents of delivery of karmaphala, who operate throug=\r\nh other people who act as physical agents of delivery!). The karma pools ma=\r\ny be re-arranged as a result. Some undesirable karmas may be downgraded to =\r\na lower pool or pushed down in order within the same pool. Or, some desirab=\r\nle karmas may be upgraded to a higher pool or pushed up in order within the=\r\n same pool.\n&gt;=C2=A0When someone curses or blesses one, with sufficient ment=\r\nal force behind it (this is the key), the same thing can happen. It is all =\r\nabout re-arranging karmas between the karmik pools. Every action by one, or=\r\n even people around one, has the potential to re-arrange one&#39;s karmik pools=\r\n. A karma about to give karmaphala may be postponed or a karma that was not=\r\n to give karmaphala anytime soon may be advanced sooner.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;However, =\r\nremember that the remedial measure has to be as intense as the karma that i=\r\nt is trying to manipulate. You can move a small rock with small force, but =\r\nyou need a large force to move a big rock or a hill.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;\n&gt;If there is=\r\n no negative karma in one&#39;s pool that can give a specific result, nobody ca=\r\nn make one experience that result, no matter what ritual one does. However,=\r\n even great souls have a lot of negative karmas in their optional pool and =\r\neven evil people have a lot of positive karmas in their optional pool, and =\r\nhence powerful remedies, curses and blessings can often make some differenc=\r\ne.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;This point is well illustrated by the &quot;Guru Charitra&quot; story Dig=\r\namber ji referred in his point (3).\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;If o=\r\nne thinks that one can escape the fruits of one&#39;s actions, one is mistakene=\r\nd. God is not like us human beings, who may show favoritism towards those w=\r\nho praise them or bribe them. The He-aspect of God is a witness to the play=\r\n of actions and fruits. The She-aspect of God is the power that impartially=\r\n and impassionately manages the fine balance and order within this play of =\r\nactions and fruits. All beings are equal in Her eyes, from the lowest of ev=\r\nil persons to the noblest of saints. She administers just and balanced deli=\r\nvery of fruits to actions using available agents.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;The karmas we co=\r\nmmitted in the past are already in the pipeline and will give their results=\r\n sooner or later. The best we can do with them, with some effort, is to per=\r\nhaps reorder them somewhat. The most important thing is to not add more ser=\r\nious bad karmas to the pipeline now. Simply put, selfish actions and action=\r\ns that cause pain or harm to others are bad karmas and selfless actions and=\r\n actions that cause pleasure or benefit to others are good karmas.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n=\r\n&gt;When it comes to manipulating the pre-existing pipeline of karmas awaiting=\r\n karmaphala, through conscious effort and current action, yes, it is possib=\r\nle and general guidelines are available in shastras, but we can&#39;t be certai=\r\nn about the specific impact of each action. One thing is for sure - remedia=\r\nl measure for overcoming a karma has to be commensurate with the karma\n its=\r\nelf.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;You need only small force to push a cat out of your way, but =\r\nneed a large force to push an elephant.\n&gt;\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;Best regards,\n&gt;Narasimha=\r\n\n&gt;--------\n&gt;Astrology & Spirituality Resources: http://www.VedicAstrologer.=\r\norg\n&gt;--------\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;\n&gt;&gt;________________________________\n&gt;&gt; From: Ajit Kr=\r\nishnan &lt;ajit.krishnan@...&gt;\n&gt;&gt;To: vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com \n&gt;&gt;Sent=\r\n: Tuesday, February 26, 2013 11:29 PM\n&gt;&gt;Subject: Re: [vedic-wisdom] few que=\r\nstions\n&gt;&gt; \n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0 \n&gt;&gt;Dear=C2=A0Digamber,\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;When a kingdom had no=\r\n royal heirs, a special elephant was appointed by the courtiers to randomly=\r\n pick the next king. Thus, it was possible for a beggar to suddenly find hi=\r\nmself the king. Whose karma is this?=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;Vasishtha gives two answ=\r\ners: (1) This is the karma of the ministers, king, and all the citizens, an=\r\nd (2) This is the karma of the beggar turned king.\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;Everything is in=\r\nterrelated. The beggar&#39;s karma made him a king. The elephant&#39;s karma allowe=\r\nd him to be the one chosen to pick the king. The minister&#39;s karma allowed t=\r\nhem to appoint the elephant to pick the king. And the citizens&#39; karma allow=\r\ned them to live in such a kingdom, and accept the result.\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;The sansk=\r\nrit word &quot;shaapa&quot; means a curse, or promise, or oath. Many of the curses th=\r\nat we see are for the benefit of mankind, and are actually blessings. At th=\r\ne end of the day, some people with a certain amount of purity of speech dis=\r\ncharge their tapas shakti through speech.\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;When it comes to people a=\r\nnd their karmic pipeline, we usually make an assumption. We assume that the=\r\nre is a person, and separate from the person are his many kar