hen want someone to come and remove all the &quot;bad&quot; =\r\nkarmas from our karmic pipeline.&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Vasishtha teach=\r\nes us that a &#39;person&#39; and &#39;karma&#39; are the same thing. You are your karmas. =\r\nAnd you are nothing but your mind-impressions ... your vaasanaas. In other =\r\nwords, your vaasanaas are your karmas.&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;If you ca=\r\nn change your vaasanaas, you have changed your karma. Or course, that is ea=\r\nsier said than done.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Any moment when your mind bec=\r\nomes quiet is a blessing. Any moment when your mind becomes agitated is a c=\r\nurse. As sadhakas, we run after quieting the mind !&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;=\r\ndiv&gt;sasneham,&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp; &nbsp;ajit&lt;/div&gt;&lt;=\r\n/div&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;div class=3D&quot;yiv1788388150gmail_quote&quot;&gt;On Tue, Feb 26, 2013 at 8=\r\n:08 AM,  &lt;span dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;&lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot; ymailto=3D&quot;mailto:dgporo=\r\nb@...&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot; href=3D&quot;mailto:dgporob@...&quot;&gt;dgporob@ya=\r\nhoo.com&lt;/a&gt;&gt;&lt;/span&gt; wrote:&lt;br&gt;&lt;blockquote class=3D&quot;yiv1788388150gmail_qu=\r\note&quot; style=3D&quot;border-left:1px #ccc solid;&quot;&gt;\n\nDear Narasimha Ji,&lt;br&gt;\n&nbsp; =\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; I was pondering over few things we routinely come acro=\r\nss as a part of worship and how it manipulates karma pipe line,&lt;br&gt;\n(1) Whe=\r\nn someone gives a `curse&#39; or does a prayoga such as `maran&#39; or `uchhatan&#39; w=\r\nhat happens to a person who is at receiving end, does his bad karma comes f=\r\norward or is it a new parabdha that is created. I vaguely remember Vimalana=\r\nnda mentioning something about a Saint&#39;s curse in Aghora trilogy.&lt;br&gt;\